'''Urban science''' is an interdisciplinary field that studies diverse [[urban area|urban]] issues and problems. Based on research findings of various disciplines such as history, economics, [[sociology]], [[Public administration|administration]], [[architecture]], [[urban engineering]], [[transportation engineering]], [[landscape]] architecture, [[environmental engineering]], and [[geo-informatics]], it aims to produce both theoretical and practical knowledge that contributes to understanding and solving the problems of urban issues in [[contemporary society]].

