'''William Walter Smith''' (14 September 1852 &ndash; 3 March 1942) was a New Zealand gardener, naturalist and conservationist. He was born in [[Hawick]], [[Roxburghshire]], Scotland in 1852. He was the initial person in charge of implementing the Scenery Preservation Act of 1903, which led to the creation of scenic and historic reserves.<ref name="DNZB Smith">{{DNZB|Galbreath|Ross|3s27|William Walter Smith|December 2011}}</ref>

